## Code Standards

**What I care about most:**
- [e.g. "No duplication — always check if something exists before creating it"]
- [e.g. "Tests are not optional — every public method has a spec"]
- [e.g. "Naming must be explicit — no abbreviations except well-known ones"]
- [e.g. "Service objects for anything with more than 2 steps of business logic"]
- [e.g. "Background jobs for anything that takes > 500ms"]

**What NOT to do:**
- [e.g. "Never put business logic in controllers"]
- [e.g. "Never call external APIs synchronously in a request cycle"]
- [e.g. "Never use raw strings for error messages — use I18n"]

---

## Testing Standards

- Tests live in `[spec/ / tests/ / __tests__/]`
- Test files mirror source structure
- Each test file covers one class/module
- No real database calls in unit tests — use doubles/mocks
- Integration tests can hit the database
- Every bug fix includes a regression test

